The truth and confidence in your words seem to cut through Bram's panic. He exhales a shaky breath and nods, his shoulders slumping in a mixture of defeat and relief. "You're right. Of course, you're right. Forgive me." With trembling fingers, he unties the small leather pouch from his belt and carefully counts out ten gold coins onto the sticky tabletop. The clinking sound seems unnaturally loud in the tavern.

