Bram looks utterly spent, but a sliver of hope has returned to his eyes. "They went east, into the woods. Darkhollow Cave... it's about a half-day's journey. May the gods watch over you." He gives you a final, pleading look before stumbling toward a vacant chair by the hearth, burying his face in his hands. The path ahead is clear: the caves lie to the east. You can speak to others in the tavern, or head outside to the village square when you are ready.

