Marcus studies you, his flinty eyes seeming to weigh your worth. A slow grunt escapes him, a sound of grudging concession. "Fine," he says, the word clipped. "Fifteen. But you better pull your weight. If I have to do all the work, I'm taking the rest of the farmer's pay as a bonus." He extends a large, calloused hand over the table, palm up.

